description:
# Conditional Statements in C#

Programs need to make decisions based on conditions. C# provides powerful tools for this!

## The if Statement

```csharp
int health = 100;

if (health > 0)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Player is alive!");
}
```

**C# Style Notes:**
- Conditions are in parentheses `()`
- Code blocks are in curly braces `{}`
- Braces are optional for single statements, but recommended

## if/else

```csharp
if (score >= 100)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Victory!");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine("Try again!");
}
```

## if/else if/else

```csharp
if (temperature > 30)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Hot!");
}
else if (temperature > 20)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Warm");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine("Cold!");
}
```

## Comparison Operators

- `==` equals (note: double equals for comparison!)
- `!=` not equals
- `>` greater than
- `<` less than
- `>=` greater than or equal
- `<=` less than or equal
- `&&` logical AND
- `||` logical OR
- `!` logical NOT

## Your Quest

Create an item rarity checker!

1. Create an `int itemValue = 750`
2. Write conditional logic:
   - If `itemValue >= 1000`: print "Legendary Item!"
   - Else if `itemValue >= 500`: print "Rare Item!"
   - Else if `itemValue >= 100`: print "Common Item"
   - Else: print "Junk Item"

**Expected output:**
```
Rare Item!
```

solutionCode:
// Create the itemValue variable
int itemValue = 750;

// Write your conditional logic
if (itemValue >= 1000)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Legendary Item!");
}
else if (itemValue >= 500)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Rare Item!");
}
else if (itemValue >= 100)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Common Item");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine("Junk Item");
}
